is mediation. Written by a diverse group of authors in interpretive sociology, this ambitious volume asks what the relationship between meaning systems and action is, how we can describe culture and which roles we assign to language, social processes and cognition in a sociological context. Contributors offer empirical research that not only outlines the conceptual issues at stake, but also demonstrates ‘how to do things’ with semiotics through case studies. Synthesizing a diverse and fragmented landscape, this is a key reference work for scholars interested in the connection between semiotics and sociology.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aSemioticsxSocial aspects. 0aSemiotics. 0aSociologyxMethodology. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / Social Theory.2bisacsh1 aBakker, J.I. (Hans), econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrekhus, Wayne H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCossu, Andrea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCossu, Andrea, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFontdevila, Jorge, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFontdevila, Jorge, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMadigan, Todd, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcLean, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRaud, Rein, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSong, Eunkyung, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWissinger, Elizabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z97831111967940 cprintz978152921175740uhttps://